{{Unreferenced|date=November 2009}} {{Views}} [[File:Frosch2Fluchtpunkte.png|thumb|left|Worm's-eye view with two vanishing points]] A '''worm's-eye view''' is a [[Perspective (visual)|view]] of an object from below, as though the [[observation|observer]] were a [[earthworm|worm]]; the opposite of a [[bird's-eye view]]. A worm's eye view is used commonly for third perspective, with one vanishing point on top, one on the left, and one on the right.
It can be used to look up to something to make an object look tall, strong, and mighty.
